## API checks (curl)

| Endpoint | Method | Result |
|---|---|---|
| `/health` | GET | `{"status":"ok","version":"1.0.0"}` -- 200 |
| `/api/edtech/login` (parent@demo.edu / ParentDemo1) | POST | JWT returned, role=parent, name=Robert Johnson |
| `/api/edtech/login` (teacher@demo.edu / TeachDemo1) | POST | JWT returned, role=teacher, name=Mrs. Rivera |
| `/api/edtech/student` (parent token) | GET | `Alex Johnson, Grade 7, teacher: Mrs. Rivera` |
| `/api/edtech/grades` (parent token) | GET | 6 grades returned (Math A+, English B+, Science A-, History B, Art A, PE A+) |
| `/api/edtech/activities` (parent token) | GET | 4 activities returned |
| `/api/edtech/messages` (parent token) | GET | 2 messages returned |
| `/api/edtech/messages/unread-count` (parent token) | GET | `{"unread":1}` |
| `/api/edtech/student` (teacher token) | GET | Alex Johnson returned |
| `/api/edtech/grades/1` (teacher token, PATCH) | PATCH | Grade updated to A+/99, `updated_at` refreshed |
| `/api/edtech/activities` (teacher token, POST) | POST | New activity created (id=5, 201 status) |
| `/api/edtech/messages` (parent token, POST) | POST | New message created (id=3, 201 status) |

All API endpoints returned correct data with no errors.

